      • list

        public CustomizationSpecs.ListInvocation list()
        Description copied from interface: CustomizationSpecs
        Returns information about at most 1000 visible (subject to permission checks) guest customization specifications in vCenter matching the CustomizationSpecsTypes.FilterSpec. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.1.

        Invocation Result:
        Commonly used information about the guest customization specifications matching the CustomizationSpecsTypes.FilterSpec.

        Operation Errors:
        InvalidArgument - if the CustomizationSpecsTypes.FilterSpec.getOSType() property contains a value that is not supported by the server.
        UnableToAllocateResource - if more than 1000 guest customization specifications match the CustomizationSpecsTypes.FilterSpec.
        ServiceUnavailable - if the system is unable to communicate with a service to complete the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have the required privileges.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:

        • Method execution requires VirtualMachine.Provisioning.ReadCustSpecs.

        Specified by:
        list in interface CustomizationSpecs
        Returns:
        instance of CustomizationSpecs.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
